Description: VOCCA is a simple Plug & Play Voice Activated Bulb Adapter which requires no wi-fi, no set-up, no installation.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: The VOCCA is a voice-activated light bulb that makes it possible to switch on the light from anywhere in your house efficiently. Unlike smart bulbs, VOCCA eliminates the hassle of having to pull out your smartphone and operate the light through another gadget. VOCCA is on 24/7 in search of the trigger phrase.  Once found, it commands its relay to transfer the power from the mains to your light bulb and voila – there’s light (or darkness). VOCCA is focused on real life application rather than being “cool” for a week.  Anyone can install VOCCA, as it requires no wifi, no hub and no configuration. The regular light switch still works when VOCCA is connected so habits don't need to change. It's a product for life as you don't need to buy a new one when your bulb dies. VOCCA uses some of the best technology to date. VOCCA is based on voice recognition technology from Sensory Inc., the world's leading voice recognition technology company. VOCCA Pro uses TobyRich Bluetooth Smart and Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE) app design. VOCCA uses Bluetooth LE to connect to an app on your smartphone. VOCCA screws in between the original volt socket and the light bulb, and comes equipped with a microphone and a Bluetooth chip. You can set trigger commands for turning the lights on and off within the app, and then you're all set — no installation, no wifi setup.

Description: Evidence-based cloud provider research
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: FY/c provides cloud buyers with evidence-based, Big Data-generated, unbiased research into how cloud providers actually perform, not how their marketing says they will perform.  Our proprietary artificial intelligence (AI) algorithms hoover up information from all over the Web. We then apply the science of service quality to transform that data into actionable intelligence. The result is a performance report that is free of the inherent human bias so common in other cloud provider review sites and analyst reports. FY/c's reporting does this by looking at all of the evidence to come up a determination of service performance. FY/c also uses it's algorithms to help buyers figure out which attributes -- not features -- of a cloud service such as high security or 24/7 support are right for them. This needs assessment tool asks buyers a series of questions that focus not on particular feature set but on the appropriateness of the service for their company. This knowledge helps buyers choose the right provider for their needs, not on their wants. As cloud-provided software and services become the norm, choosing the right cloud provider can mean the difference between a business reaching its goals or not. FY/c is determined to help its users be part of the first group, not the second.
Industry Groups: Artificial Intelligence (AI), Data and Analytics, Information Technology, Internet Services, Science and Engineering, Software

It's a natural solution for future treatments. Stem cells are special cells that are able to grow into various other types of more specialized cells. Mesenchymal stem cells are multipotent stem cells that can differentiate into a variety of cell types including cartilage, bone, tendon, ligaments, fat, marrow, CNS, skin, and muscles. Stem cells also have what is called immunoprivilege. That means that they will not be attacked by the host's immune system, unlike other types of foreign tissues. Stem cells are thus able to potentially treat many diseases that normally would not be feasible to treat with standard procedures.

Description: SensorWare Systems, Inc., located in Pasadena, California, is a leader in embedded monitoring/control systems.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: SensorWare Systems, Inc., located in Pasadena, California, is a leader in embedded monitoring/control systems.  It was formed in 2006 to commercialize the patented wireless sensor infrastructure technology developed at NASA for the Department of Homeland Security by company founder, Dr. Kevin Delin. SensorWare Systems provides solutions for active, real-time situational awareness and decision making.  The technological core of these solutions, the Sensor Web, consists of a collection of small sensor platforms (pods) connected to sensors which measure environmental parameters.  These pods are spread across a geographical area and communicate with each other wirelessly.  Unlike mesh networks, there are no routers or gateways; the Sensor Web is a single, distributed instrument.  Every pod knows all the data across the system and can act as a portal.  Each pod is like a pixel in the snapshot the Sensor Web takes.  This form of communication gives the Sensor Web unprecedented power in in-field interpretation of and reacting to a dynamically changing environment. Sensor Webs have been fielded by first responders monitoring hazardous gases and structural integrity in compromised buildings and by the EPA in decontamination operations.  Because any sensor can be connected to a pod, Sensor Webs are also valuable for environmental conservation and management solutions including water resource management and enabling green solutions of power generation.  The turn-key systems require little training and seamlessly integrate with remote decision tools.  Additional information about some of SensorWare Systems' over 30 real-world deployments in demanding environments, as well as live, streaming data from current deployments, can be found at www.SensorWareSystems.com.
Industry Groups: Agriculture and Farming, Privacy and Security

Additionally, Fitcasts: - Allows members to watch and use a workout video simultaneously with up to 9 people using Fitcasts Hangout video call - Is useable on any mobile device (smartphones & tablets) and is compatible with Google Chromecast - Gives users the ability to create their own customizable workout program using Fitcasts videos  - Provides tools to help people track the progress of their health - Suggests other videos by the same trainer when a user views a video by that trainer - Allows users to save videos for later use by "favoriting" them Fitcasts not only makes life easier for people looking for workout videos but also gives trainers a resource that allows their fans/members to use their videos in more dynamic ways.
